-- Hungary Stocks: Magyar Telekom, CIG Pannonia Move in Budapest
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-04-20T15:37:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-20/hungary-stocks-e-star-alternativ-cig-pannonia-move-in-budapest.html
Hungary ’s benchmark  BUX (BUX)  stock index
fell 0.2 percent to 17,511.01 by the close in Budapest.  The following were among the most active shares in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Magyar Telekom Nyrt. (MTEL)  , Hungary’s former phone
monopoly, fell the most in more than three months after news
website Origo reported that the government plans to tax phone
and internet usage. The shares dropped 2.4 percent to 538
forint, the biggest decline since Jan. 5.  CIG Pannonia Eletbiztosito Nyrt. (PANNONIA HB), a Hungarian
life insurer, slumped for a second day, reaching a record low
after shareholders yesterday authorized the board to raise
capital. The shares dropped 2.8 percent to 380 forint.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
